The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Alstom, Bhel in tie-up

 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT 

 Chennai, April 5: The Tiruchirappalli unit of Bharat Heavy Electricals has entered into an agreement with Alstom of France to make super-critical boilers. 

 Alstom will provide the technology to build these boilers, which will help meet the countrys additional power demand.

 V. Gopalakrishna, executive director of Bhels Trichy unit, said around Rs 190 crore will be pumped into this complex in the current financial year to increase the capacity from the present 4,000 mw to 5,750 mw. To meet the increased demand and to complete projects in the shortest possible time, Bhel has been pursuing new concepts like site fabrication action to promote bulk supplies, he said. 




